Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat. 2. Add minced garlic and diced onion, cook until softened. 3. Push garlic and onion to one side of the skillet and crack eggs into the empty space. Scramble until cooked. 4. Add diced carrots and peas, cook until tender. 5. Stir in diced pineapple, peeled and deveined shrimp, and cooked rice. 6. Add soy sauce and fish sauce, toss to combine. 7. Cook until everything is heated through. 8. Garnish with cashew nuts. 9.
